In order to show or hide code lenses for the [Version Lens](https://github.com/vscode-contrib/vscode-versionlens) extension via the toolbar

![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1727302/25784531/b68fe150-3366-11e7-8ac6-d262fb992fac.png)

I'm having to turn disable code lenses and re-enable them again with a timeout like this:

```js

export function showVersionLenses(file) {
  appSettings.showVersionLenses = true;
  utils.refreshCodeLens();
}

export function hideVersionLenses(file) {
  appSettings.showVersionLenses = false;
  utils.refreshCodeLens();
}

...utils.js
const key = 'editor.codeLens';

// turn off codelens
workspaceConfiguration.update(key, false, true);

// turn on code lens after 500 ms
setTimeout(function () {
  // turn on codelens to refesh them
  workspaceConfiguration.update(key, true, true);
}, 500);
...

```

This works but it has to turn off all code lens providers in order to re-invoke the `provider.provideCodeLenses` function.

Would be great to have an exposed api that does this but only for specific providers.

Something like:

```js
editor.toggleCodelenses(show: boolean, providerTypeToToggle: CodeLensProviderType);
```
